  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Radiographer",
  "description": "<p><strong>Roles & Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Perform diagnostic imaging examinations to produce accurate, high-quality images for clinical diagnosis.</li></ul><ul><li>Work independently to operate imaging equipment safely and effectively, including Mammography, X-Ray, BMD.</li></ul><ul><li>Provide quality care to patient who comes for any imaging procedure including a comprehensive assessment of the patient before each ultrasonography/ radiography and careful monitoring during and after the procedure until safe discharge from the centre.</li></ul><ul><li>Participate in team discussions for the purpose of process improvement, professional and personal development and to be a good team player while maintaining a safe and healthy environment among colleagues.</li></ul><ul><li>Continuous self-development through continuing education and training in order to keep up to date with current trends in Radiography.</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements</strong></p><ul><li>Degree in Radiography or equivalent</li><li>Registered with the Allied Health Professions Council (AHPC) Singapore </li><li>Minimum 15 years of relevant experience </li><li>Strong communication and interpersonal skills</li><li>Able to work independently and as part of a team</li></ul><p><br /></p>",
